{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17493383","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17493383"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T07:08:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T07:08:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1307"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1307","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1307"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.08,0.06,0.24,0.54]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1307"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"59257"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1307","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1307"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1307"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44668"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"29"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"390"},{"type":"tags","id":"1181"},{"type":"tags","id":"1432"},{"type":"tags","id":"2098"},{"type":"tags","id":"2163"},{"type":"tags","id":"2445"},{"type":"tags","id":"2746"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"7005"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"8218"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3713"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18582"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42281"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44576"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45064"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"59257","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/59257"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 48-year-old woman presents to her General Practice clinic with a swelling in her neck that had been present for three weeks. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. She has a family history of Hashimoto\u0027s thyroiditis. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination she appears well. Thyroid examination shows a 1.5 cm firm swelling with ill-defined borders in the left lobe of the thyroid gland. There is no cervical lymphadenopathy. Her thyroid function tests show TSH 0.89 mIU/L (0.5 \u2013 3.7) and free T4 17 pmol/L (10 \u2013 25). An ultrasound demonstrates a hypoechoic swelling in an otherwise normal-looking thyroid gland. Fine needle aspiration cytology shows large thyrocytes with an abnormal nucleus and cytoplasm with several mitoses and psammoma bodies present.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following findings would be expected on a radioisotope scan?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Normal activity","Diffuse increased uptake","Diminished overall activity","Focal increased uptake","Cold nodule"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe clinical picture is concerning for a malignant thyroid nodule, likely papillary thyroid cancer given the presence of psammoma bodies. Suggestive features include the rapidly growing neck mass on history, ill-defined borders on examination, hypoechoic lesion on ultrasound and FNA findings. Thyroid cancers are usually non-secreting and therefore will not demonstrate any activity on a radioisotope scan. This would appear as a so-called \u003Cstrong\u003Ecold nodule\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA subnormal serum TSH would indicate hyperthyroidism which increases the likelihood of a hyperfunctioning nodule which would show \u003Cstrong\u003Efocal increased uptake\u003C/strong\u003E, however our patient is euthyroid. There is a solitary nodule on exam and ultrasound, therefore scintigraphy findings will likely show a discrete finding rather than \u003Cstrong\u003Ediminished overall activity\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003Ediffuse increased uptake\u003C/strong\u003E. Given the clinical picture of a likely thyroid cancer, \u003Cstrong\u003Enormal activity \u003C/strong\u003Ewould not be expected. \u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Thyroid cancers usually appear as a \u0027cold nodule\u0027 on thyroid scintigraphy as they are often nonfunctioning / nonsecreting."],"references":["Bailey S, Wallwork B. Differentiating between benign and malignant thyroid nodules: An evidence-based approach in general practice.  Aust J Gen Prac 2018; 47:770-74. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31207674/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44668"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1307"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44668","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/44668"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-05T22:51:18+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-05T22:52:04+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1307"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"59257"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"positi